# RiftView CODEOWNERS — supply-chain & build-system-critical files.
#
# Rationale (RIFT-110 supply-chain audit, post-merge addendum to RIFT-70):
# the `lockfile-override-approved` label is the audit-trail-friendly escape
# hatch for the lockfile-change CI guard. Without an approval gate, any
# write-access user can apply the label and bypass the guard. CODEOWNERS
# names the supply-chain owners; `.github/workflows/lockfile-override-gate.yml`
# enforces that the override label requires an approving review from a
# non-author owner of pnpm-lock.yaml.
#
# Standard CODEOWNERS semantics: last matching pattern wins. Add the most
# specific rules at the bottom.

# Default owners — every path falls back to the maintainer set.
*                       @3urkii @juliushamm

